The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at a Republican rally in Louisiana. Pence thanked the audience for their support and urged them to vote for Republican candidates in the upcoming elections, including the race for governor. He highlighted the achievements of the Trump administration, such as tax cuts, job creation, military investment, and border security. Pence also criticized the Democratic Party, calling them "left-wing radicals" who advocate for socialism and open borders. He encouraged the audience to spread the message of Republican achievements and to pray for America.